item.title: Daniel Snyder
item.dc:creator: leoluong
item.content:encoded: Daniel Snyder is currently pursuing his Bachelors in Exercise Science from Old Dominion University (ODU) with plans of pursuing his Masters in Exercise Physiology. He is a Certified Personal Trainer through the International Sports Science Association (ISSA). He is the owner and operator of his own business, Snyder Strong LLC. Science has always been a big part of his life, as a result, he has incorporated a scientific approach in training his clients to achieve the best results possible. He is currently serving in the United States Army Reserves (USAR), he takes his drive and determination from the USAR and brings it to his clients to keep them striving to achieve beyond their goals. Daniel had always been a heavy set individual for most of his life, one day he decided to make a change for the better. He had started his fitness journey at the weight of 197lbs and just months later he was weighing in at 164lbs and the leanest he had ever been. Daniel loves helping people better their lives, so the Personal Training field is the perfect fit for him. He plans on changing the Fitness industry for the better, follow him on his journey to the top!

item.title: Brian Lewis
item.dc:creator: leoluong
item.content:encoded: Fitness and lifting weights has always been the main focus in my life. Starting with sports at a young age then on into High School where I began weight lifting in my basement to gain strength for football. In High School, I won two State Championships in football and was a champion sprinter in track. Following High School, I began training for Rescue Swimmer in the United States Navy. Shortly after getting out of the Navy I started Powerlifting and won competitions at the 165 lb weight class. I've always lifted weights but never had the appearance I've wanted. I began to transform myself through nutrition. I was amazed to see the changes my body made by eating right so I began finding ways to get as lean as possible the healthy and drug free way. From there I started my adventure as a natural Men's Physique competitor. I competed in my first competition in the fall of 2012 and have competed seven times since then. I currently compete in the NPC at the national level and my goal is to turn IFBB pro. It would be an amazing accomplishment for me to turn pro as a drug free athlete and to set an example for future athletes that you don't need to turn to steroids to reach your dreams. Aside from competing, my focus is being the best personal trainer and coach that I can be. I'm in a position to change peoples lives. It's very rewarding to see the positive changes in my clients. I can't tell you how many times I've sat down and just thought about how many people I have an impact on and it's very touching to see that I can motivate so many! I love what I do and it's very exciting to think of what I can accomplish in this industry!

item.title: Tayvion Baker
item.dc:creator: leoluong
item.content:encoded: BODYBYTAY was created by personal trainer and fitness model Tayvion Baker. Being fit, staying fit and helping others do the same has been his life-long passion. Whether you are trying to lose a significant amount of weight for a complete lifestyle change or just trying to lose a few inches for that special occasion, he is definitely the guy you want by your side. He will guide you through his various work-out routines and meal plans and help you choose the one that will best suit your needs. Come join #TEAMBODYBYTAY and you will be on a road to a more fit and healthier lifestyle in no time!
